physical_appearance: This is a black-and-white photograph. It is rectangular in shape and landscape in orientation. It features a body of water in the foreground. In the background, along the edge of the waterbody, there are several buildings seen. They are of varied architecture and height. The buildings are interspersed with trees and greenery. The photograph is quite blurry. There are no tears or folds seen on the photograph.
sgcool_label_text: This is a personal photograph album that belonged to a Corporal A. Silver who spent 16 months in Singapore between 1951 and 1952. Silver was presumably a Jewish lady who was stationed in Singapore to serve at the Royal Air Force (RAF) Hospital at Changi. The album contains photographs that document her working and personal life, including friends she made within the Jewish community in Singapore.
title_text: "Personal photograph album titled ""Sixteen Months in Singapore""" Sixteen Months in Singapore: Photograph of buildings along a body of water
